snippet.textDisplay:
1968 flu pandemic
The 1968 flu pandemic was a category 2 flu pandemic whose outbreak in 1968 and 1969 killed an estimated one million people worldwide. It was caused by an H3N2 strain of the influenza A virus, descended from H2N2 through antigenic shift, a genetic process in which genes from multiple sub-types re-assorted to form a new virus. Because it originated in Hong Kong, the pandemic is also referred to as Hong Kong flu.
